# Commit message summary

## End of work that changed the repository

After implementation that changed files, draft a summary only (do **not** commit or push unless the user asked):

- Run `git status`, `git diff`, and `git diff --staged` (in parallel when practical)
- Summarize changes in 2–5 bullets (what / why), then append a recommended commit footer
- Use conventional type prefixes (`feat`, `fix`, `style`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`)
- Skip the commit block on question-only / review-only turns with **no** file changes, or when the user asks not to include one

## When the user invokes `/commit-message`

Follow `.cursor/skills/commit-message/SKILL.md` in full:

- Summarize and draft the message
- Then **always** run `git add`, `git commit`, and `git push`
- Never stop at a copy-paste-only draft for `/commit-message`
